STATE EX REL. FREED
v.
DREXEL 2018-0609 Supreme Court of Ohio. January 23, 2019

CASE ANNOUNCEMENTS

MOTION AND PROCEDURAL RULINGS

In Mandamus. On relator's motions for Ohio Constitution, Article IV, Section 2 (C) "Reasons Therefor," to reverse denial of due process, to withdraw or strike erroneous filing, and for judicial notice. Motions denied.

French, DeWine, and Stewart, JJ., would grant relator's motion to strike erroneous filing.
